The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their performance on visual recognition problems, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new architecture for CNNs that incorporates a memory mechanism, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the vanishing or exploding gradient problem, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed architecture on benchmark datasets, which is a common topic in natural language processing and computer vision (cs.CL).
